>> What are the key downstream pathways regulated by p53 in acute
>> In acute myeloid leukemia blasts, p53 primarily regulates apoptosis
It activates the p21 (CDKN1A) pathway to induce
G1/S phase arrest and promotes apoptosis through BAX and PUMA
Recent studies also show that p53 directly activates the
PI3K/AKT/mTOR pathway to enhance autophagy in AML cells.....
